Steve,

Cl.exe is the Microsoft C/C++ compiler. What version are you using?

I put the executable for this example program 'examples.exe' in zipped
form on the Cantera download site. It is in directory 'examples/cxx'. It
should run without needing any other DLL files. It does need a few data
files, so you need to have the 'data' directory present and CANTERA_ROOT
set. I have also put the data directory on the download site, so you can
get any individual files you need.

Perhaps try that and see if it runs on your system. If it runs ok, then
my guess is that you have some problem with your compiler configuration.

Dave
